message.content:
The other two experiments also required the same number of test tubes. Since Sara needed a total of 8 test tubes for all three experiments and the first experiment used 2, you can find the number of test tubes needed for each of the other two experiments by subtracting the number of test tubes used in the first experiment from the total:

8 (total test tubes) - 2 (test tubes for the first experiment) = 6 test tubes

So, each of the other two experiments required 6 test tubes.
